# Walkthrough - GitHub & Vercel Deployment

We have successfully published the **Avani Loan Agents** project to GitHub and deployed it to production on Vercel.

---

## 🛠️ Summary of Actions

### 1. Repository Setup & Protection
* **Git Ignore (`.gitignore`)**: Created a standard Next.js `.gitignore` file to ensure local databases (`database.db`), local secrets (`.env.local`), and build artifacts are kept secure and never pushed publicly.
* **Initial Commit**: Initialized git and committed the project files.
* **GitHub Push**: Created a new public repository and pushed the code to:
  🔗 [GitHub Repository](https://github.com/avaniagrofoods/avani-loan-agents)

### 2. Next.js Upgrade & Vercel Deploy Gate Resolution
* **The Issue**: Vercel rejected the initial build command, citing a vulnerability check failure on `next@15.1.0`.
* **The Fix**: Upgraded Next.js to the latest stable version (`16.2.9`), which cleared the Vercel security gate.
* **Production Deployment**: Linked the project and successfully deployed it to Vercel production.
  🔗 [Live Production URL](https://avani-loan-agents.vercel.app)

